Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join, downturning. Clay near fine, micaceous, purplish buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0176) (A piece from Miletus, not from the same stamp, with EO[ is discussed by Joehrens, AA 2014, 187, no.58, with niotes on examples of Eo- for Eu- on Kos and in Ionia.)
